
SimpleArray is a subclass of BasicArray that adds IO stream operators and 
logical operators to this class.  The constructors for SimpleArray have the
same semantics as the constructors for BasicArray.

int  operator== (const SimpleArray<T>& array);

  Returns TRUE(1) if every element in 'array' is equal to its corresponding 
  element in ArrayData.

int  operator!= (const SimpleArray<T>& array);

  Returns FALSE(0) if at least one element in 'array' is not equal to its 
  corresponding element in ArrayData.

int write(ostream& output) const;

  Writes the array to 'output'

int read(istream& input);

  Reads an array from 'input'.  This method is not currently implemented.

int write(PackBuffer& output) const;

  Packs the array into 'output'

int read(UnPackBuffer& input);

  Unpacks an array from 'input'.

ostream& operator<<(ostream& output, const SimpleArray<T>& array)

  A stream operator that calls the 'write' method.
 
istream& operator>>(istream& input, SimpleArray<T>& array);

  A stream operator that calls the 'read' method.

PackBuffer& operator<<(PackBuffer& output, const SimpleArray<T>& array)

  A stream operator that calls the 'write' method.
 
UnPackBuffer& operator>>(UnPackBuffer& input, SimpleArray<T>& array);

  A stream operator that calls the 'read' method.
